How to set up Google Compute Engine

Step 1: Create console.cloud.google.com account

Step 2: Enable billing, then create a budget in the billing section (left slider options)

Step 3: Create a project (top options) to receive permissions to view pages

Step 4: Create Managed Instance Group (choose regional instance to enable option for static external IP address, choose
        autoscale: on with 1 - 80 machines as 80 machines is the maximum allowed at the time of this writing, and allow
        HTTP and HTTPS traffic)
        
Step 5: Create static external IP address
